President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Alaska due to a severe storm that occurred on December 4, 2017. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas, specifically the Kenai Peninsula Borough. The Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) has named Thomas J. Dargan as the Federal Coordinating Officer for the recovery operations. Federal funding will be available on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work, facility repairs or replacements, and hazard mitigation measures statewide. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.